A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Youth Sports Safety Advisory Commission
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Youth Sports Safety Advisory Commission to study
4 and make recommendations to minimize risk and maximize safety for youth
5 athletes; and generally relating to the Youth Sports Safety Advisory Commission.
6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That:
8 (a) There is a Youth Sports Safety Advisory Commission.
9 (b) The Commission consists of the following members:
10 (1) one member of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the President of
11 the Senate;
12 (2) one member of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker of the
13 House;
14 (3) the State Superintendent of Schools, or the State Superintendent’s
15 designee; and
16 (4) the following members who have experience with youth sports safety or
17 treating youth sports injuries, appointed by the Governor:
18 (i) one representative of the Maryland Chapter of the American
19 Academy of Pediatrics;
20 (ii) one representative of the Maryland Academy of Family
21 Physicians;
